eight hours/eight-hour day
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:in reference to the duration of what was considered a fair working day within the context of the movement associated with Samuel Duncan Parnell, introduced into NZ c. 1840.  Esp. eight-hour day, eight hours movement, eight hours rule. See also eight-hour man.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
